The global indicator represents all women of reproductive age. This survey estimate represents women who are married or in a union. Unmet need data pertain to fecund married women, currently sexually active, currently exposed to the risk of pregnancy, not wanting to become pregnant, and not using a method of contraception other than folk methods, douches, breastfeeding or lactational amenorrhea (LAM). Unmet need data exclude women who are currently pregnant, currently seeking to become pregnant, subfecund, or who are not sexually active, including women practicing post-partum abstinence. Romania 2004 Reproductive and Health Survey

The global indicator represents all women of reproductive age. This survey estimate represents women who are married or in a union. Unmet need data include women who were not using contraception because of unavailability of methods or fear of side effects. Unmet need data exclude women who are not using a method of contraception due to being separated, sterile, ill, breastfeeding or pregnant, or trying to get pregnant. China 2001 National Family Planning and Reproductive Health Survey
